com.hazelcast.internal.networking.nio

Interface MigratablePipeline

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    NioInboundPipeline, NioOutboundPipeline, NioPipeline

    public interface MigratablePipeline
    A NioPipeline that supports migration between NioThread instances. This API is called by the IOBalancer.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      long load()
      Get 'load' recorded by the current pipeline.
      NioThread owner()
      Get NioThread currently owning this pipeline.
      void requestMigration(NioThread newOwner)
      Requests the MigratablePipeline to move to the new NioThread.

    • Method Detail

      • requestMigration

        void requestMigration(NioThread newOwner)
        Requests the MigratablePipeline to move to the new NioThread. This call will not wait for the migration to complete. This method can be called by any thread, and will probably be called by the IOBalancer. Call is ignored when pipeline is moving to the same NioThread.
        Parameters:
        newOwner - the NioThread that is going to own this MigratablePipeline

      • owner

        NioThread owner()
        Get NioThread currently owning this pipeline. Pipeline owner is a thread running this pipeline. IOBalancer can decide to migrate a pipeline to another owner.
        Returns:
        current owner

      • load

        long load()
        Get 'load' recorded by the current pipeline. It can be used to calculate whether this pipeline should be migrated to a different NioThread
        Returns:
        total load recorded by this pipeline
